hu.akarnokd.reactive4java.reactive

Class DefaultRunnableObserver<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • hu.akarnokd.reactive4java.reactive.DefaultRunnableObserver<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the observed type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Observer<T>, RunnableClosableObserver<T>, Closeable, AutoCloseable, Runnable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultObserver, DefaultRunnable

    public abstract class DefaultRunnableObserver<T>
extends Object
implements RunnableClosableObserver<T>
    A composite scheduler and observer class for cases when the observation is entangled with some timed schedule operation and they need to communicate with each other and deregister together.
    Author:
    akarnokd, 2011.01.30.

      • schedule

        public void schedule(Scheduler pool,
            long initialDelay,
            long delay,
            TimeUnit unit)
        Registers this instance on the given pool as a repeatable task which gets repeated at a fixed rate after an initial delay.
        Parameters:
        pool - the target scheduler pool
        initialDelay - the initial schedule delay
        delay - the delay between runs
        unit - the time unit of the initialDelay and delay parameters

      • schedule

        public void schedule(Scheduler pool)
        Submit this task to the given executor service without any scheduling requirements. If this instance has an associated future, that instance gets cancelled
        Parameters:
        pool - the target executor service

      • register

        public void register(Observable<? extends T> observable)
        Register with the given observable and store the closeable handle of this registration. If this was registered to another observable, that registration is unregistered.
        Parameters:
        observable - the target observable

      • unregister

        protected void unregister()
        Deregisters the current instance from the associated observer without affecting the scheduler part's registration. If you need to deregister both, use the close() method instead.

      • cancel

        protected void cancel()
        Cancel the scheduler part of this instance without cancelling the observable registration. If you need to deregister both, use the close() method instead.
